  "response": "Here's a guide to making a great tequila shot:\n\n1. Choose a high-quality 100% agave tequila (blanco/silver or reposado)\n\n2. Traditional shot preparation:\n- Use a lime wedge\n- Sprinkle salt on your hand between thumb and index finger\n- Lick the salt\n- Take the shot quickly\n- Bite/suck the lime after the shot\n\n3. Tips for a smooth experience:\n- Chill the tequila slightly\n- Use fresh lime\n- Use quality sea salt\n- Sip slowly if it's a premium tequila\n- Don't slam it down harshly\n\n4. Optional variations:\n- Sangrita chaser\n- Cinnamon and orange instead of salt/lime\n- Flavored salts\n- Different citrus like grapefruit\n\n5. Pro tips:\n- Room temperature tequila releases more flavor\n- Good tequila shouldn't need to be masked by salt/lime\n- Smell the tequila before drinking\n- Sip and savor high-end varieties\n\n6. Responsible drinking:\n- Drink in moderation\n- Have a designated driver\n- Stay hydrated\n\nEnjoy responsibly!",
